OL,3,CTaxi driver 'acting the hardman' jailed
OL,5,FInstead, he made the case that the
OL,6,Fitem he had was a toy, and claimed
OL,7,Fthat the two males in the taxi knew
OL,8,Fthey were being recorded and consented
OL,9,Fto the actions that took place.
OL,11,FJudge McColgan said that whilst the
OL,12,Ftwo passengers did not co-operate with
OL,13,Fthe police investigation and did not
OL,14,Fmake statements, they did not consent
OL,15,Fto what occurred.
OL,17,FCrown barrister Natalie Pinkerton set
OL,18,Fout several aggravating which included
OL,19,Fthe threat made to the front seat
OL,20,Fpassenger and an assault on the same
OL,21,Fmale with the imitation firearm.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/10
