OL,3,CTaxi driver 'acting the hardman' jailed
OL,5,FShe added that the two passengers were
OL,6,Funable to escape from the taxi during
OL,7,Fthe incident
OL,9,FDefence barrister Sean Devine,
OL,10,Finstructed by solicitor Mark Austin,
OL,11,Fbranded the case as "highly unusual"
OL,12,Fand spoke of a "supreme irony".
OL,14,FThis, he said, was that the very
OL,15,Fbehaviour Stalford was berating the
OL,16,Ffront-seat passenger about was
OL,17,Fprecisely why he found himself in that
OL,18,Fpredicament - he was working off his
OL,19,Fown debt due to a "very substantial"
OL,20,Fcocaine addiction by calling in
OL,21,Fanother debt.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/10
