OL,3,CTaxi driver 'acting the hardman' jailed
OL,5,FMr Devine also revealed that due to
OL,6,Fhis actions, Stalford both lost his
OL,7,Femployment and his long-term
OL,8,Femployability.
OL,10,FDespite his initial denials, Stalford
OL,11,Fpleaded guilty to the charge and told
OL,12,Fa Probation Officer it occurred during
OL,13,Fa chaotic period in his life.
OL,15,FHe told Probation that at the time he
OL,16,Fwas abusing cocaine on a daily basis
OL,17,Fwhich made him feel 'confident' and
OL,18,F'invincible'.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/10
