OL,5,FShe also noted that Stalford has
OL,6,Fexpressed remorse and regret for his
OL,7,Fbehaviour and has displayed victim
OL,8,Fempathy regarding the impact his
OL,9,Factions will have had on both
OL,10,Fpassengers.
OL,12,FAddressing Stalford as he stood in the
OL,13,Fdock, Judge McColgan imposed the 20-
OL,14,Fmonth sentence and told him this was
OL,15,Fbeing split equally between prison and
OL,16,Flicence.
